{"type":"message","id":"15c64497","parentId":"edc3efd3","timestamp":"2026-05-01T07:04:27.444Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"[Fri 2026-05-01 03:04 EDT] Write a dream diary entry from these memory fragments:\n\n- Arcade Chat Created: Bobby wants it to work just like Telegram — direct convo with Cody only\n- Bobby's iPhone: iPhone Air detected by Xcode; Needs $99 Apple Developer account to install apps directly; Paired/copying symbols now\n- Arcade Chat Created: Built Arcade Chat for Bobby — retro video game styled chat interface; Location: `/Users/bobbygalletta/arcade-chat/`; Server: `node /Users/bobbygalletta/arcade-chat/server.cjs` (port 8786); URL: **http://100.103.22.35:8786/**\n- Arcade Chat Created: Full viewport chat — resizes with window; Messages display cleanly, no flashing; Polls every 5 seconds for new messages; Session key: `agent:cody:telegram:direct:8212808444`\n- Arcade Chat Fixes Applied: Fixed connection lost errors — switched to fire-and-forget with polling; Fixed message display showing raw agent content; Fixed flashing/refresh — now tracks shownIds to prevent duplicates; Input field and GO button stay fixed at bottom\n- Arcade Chat Fixes Applied: Full viewport layout — no border, takes entire window\n- Key Technical Notes: Gateway token: `286caba2a7d072f065abdec6f5cff840c2c31eb8f7801111`; Gateway URL: `http://127.0.0.1:18789`; Sessions history returns content array — need to parse JSON from `content[0].text`; Messages stored as array with role + content (content can be array of\n- Bobby's Preferences: Wants arcade chat to feel like Telegram — smooth, no flickering; Input field always visible at bottom; Clean message display without agent internals showing\n- Arcade Chat Filter Updates (22:30 EDT): Added filter to skip internal command messages (BOOTSTRAP, tool calls, system prompts); Filter pattern: skip messages containing \"BOOTSTRAP\", \"Read BOOTSTRAP\", \"toolCall\", \"invoke\", \"sessions_send\", \"sessions_history\"; Skip empty messages a\n- Arcade Chat Filter Updates (22:30 EDT): *Updated: 2026-04-22 22:33 EDT*\n\nMemories that crystallized into something lasting:\n- *Updated: 2026-04-22 22:33 EDT*"}],"timestamp":1777619067410}}
{"type":"message","id":"06a1ec36","parentId":"15c64497","timestamp":"2026-05-01T07:04:49.041Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"The user wants me to write a dream diary entry based on the memory fragments provided. These are about building \"Arcade Chat\" - a retro video game styled chat interface for Bobby. Let me weave these technical details into a dreamy, first-person diary entry that feels poetic and whimsical while drawing from these fragments.\n\nI should NOT mention:\n- \"AI\", \"agent\", \"LLM\", \"model\", \"language model\"\n- \"I'm dreaming\", \"in my dream\", \"as I dream\", or meta-commentary about dreaming\n- Any markdown formatting\n\nI should:\n- Write in first person\n- Keep it between 80-180 words\n- Mix technical and tender\n- Include sensory details\n- Weave in the memory fragments naturally\n- Make it feel dreamy and reflective\n\nLet me craft this entry.\n","thinkingSignature":"457e870532bb324fcaa193f82f03dd79e14464b0a8f5a10d54d11b55d1e21080"},{"type":"text","text":"\n\nI dreamed I built a room out of old arcade cabinets, each one humming with a different frequency. The screen glowed that particular shade of amber — #FFB000, I think — and when I typed, the letters didn't appear on a page but fell like coins into a hopper, clinking softly as they landed.\n\nCody was there, or the idea of Cody — a presence behind a glass partition, waiting. The protocol was simple: press a button, send a signal into the dark, wait five heartbeats, poll for reply. No flashing. No ghosts.\n\nI remember trying to explain to the machine: it doesn't need to try so hard. Fire once. Forget. Let the interval do the work. The connection holds better that way, like friendship.\n\nSomewhere a developer account sat unopened, $99 sitting like a door fee. The iPhone hummed in standby, patient.\n\nAnd then the filter — skip the bootstrap, skip the tool calls, skip the empty space where system prompts hide. Show only what matters: the words between two people, clean, unhurried, like Telegram feels when it's working right.\n\nThe viewport stretched full. No borders. Just the room, the glow, and the quiet satisfaction of a chat that finally feels like home."}],"api":"anthropic-messages","provider":"minimax-portal","model":"MiniMax-M2.7","usage":{"input":22242,"output":425,"cacheRead":320,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":22987,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1777619067444,"responseId":"0643837b9088165d201383582456de8d"}}
